rComments: Overall a pretty solid professor. Occasionally there is some disorganization with scheduling, but its difficult to blame the professor when he needs accommodate over 250 students. Tests are very relevant to lectures, so if use the tools he gives you to learn (practice questions, online quizzes, in-class iClicker questions), youll get a good mark.

rComments: He can be a bit dis-organized but towards 2nd half of the course it's okay. Readings for the course are almost mandatory! His lecture slides are complementary and guide you to understanding what will be tested. Overall, if you do the readings and homework and listen in class, ECO358 is a good course to take with Prof McKeown.

rComments: A decent professor. Didn't do as well but solely because of mistakes in my part. His lectures could be unengaging sometimes so make sure you stay awake.
The test has nothing similar with the practice questions and he did not give us any past exams to prepare final. Avoid him at any cost!

I really think some people below give him a rough time. He gives you all the tools you need to succeed in his course, from detailed readings, practice questions, weekly quizzes, in-class iClicker questions, and notes to print out and bring to class to fill in. The material isn't easy but again, you are given specific instructions on how to do well.

rComments: Awful teacher. Super tough test. The questions on the test were structured completely different with the examples he gave us. Spending time to prepare for the tests is unnecessary because you won't be able to solve it anyways.

A great professor to inspire you for future economics in your life. Not too harsh of a grader and homework is not too hard and clear. Overall, really helps you enjoy the course and gives you a better grade than you might expect.
Took ECO202 with RJM. Great course, sometimes he was a little unprepared but it's a relatively easy course. He's really helpful in office hours and releases all practice questions and answers early

Prof. McKeown made 2nd Year Macroeconomics interesting and engaging. There was a good mix of fundamentals from the textbook and real life case study applications.   Office hours are useful. Would recommend.
